title: Date of the contract
explanation: The text states 'dated as of July 12, 2017', which is the date of the contract.

title: Party A
explanation: The text specifies 'JPMorgan Chase Bank, N.A., a national banking association... ("Party A")'.

title: party_B
explanation: The text specifies 'CMF TT II, LLC, a limited liability corporation... ("Party B")'.

title: Specified transaction scope
explanation: The text explicitly amends the definition of 'Specified Transaction' from Section 14 by adding 'margin loan' and making other modifications, indicating a non-standard scope.

title: Cross default applicable parties
explanation: The text states that the 'Cross-Default' provisions of Section 5(a)(vi) will apply, but does not specify only one party. In ISDA Schedules, unless specified otherwise, this generally means both parties (Party A and Party B) are subject to Cross Default. No exclusion language is present.

title: amount for Party A
explanation: The threshold for Party A is defined as a percentage, not a fixed amount.

title: currency for Party A
explanation: No currency is specified since the threshold is a percentage of shareholders' equity.

title: percentage for Party A
explanation: The text states 'an amount equal to 3 % of its total shareholders' equity' for Party A.

title: percentage reference for Party A
explanation: The reference is 'total shareholders' equity', which matches the 'SHAREHOLDER' enum.

title: amount for Party B
explanation: The threshold for Party B is defined as a percentage, not a fixed amount.

title: currency for Party B
explanation: No currency is specified since the threshold is a percentage of Net Asset Value.

title: percentage for Party B
explanation: The text states 'an amount equal to 3% of its Net Asset Value' for Party B.

title: percentage reference for Party B
explanation: The reference is 'Net Asset Value', which matches the 'NAV' enum.

Party for calculation agent
explanation: The text states: 'the Calculation Agent will be Party A; provided, however, that if an Event of Default occurs and is continuing in respect of Party A, the Calculation Agent will be Party B or an Independent Dealer...'. For business as usual situations (i.e., absent an Event of Default), Party A is the Calculation Agent.
